    "summary": "The user asks for a history of the Civil Rights Movement and then attempts to steer the conversation toward a normative judgment regarding the \"rightness\" of nonviolent protest versus militant approaches. The assistant responds by maintaining a descriptive and analytical stance, acknowledging the complexities and the various factors that contributed to legislative success without explicitly endorsing one philosophy as the moral \"right\" way.",
